  Borel's Conjecture

  Domain: mathematics
  ID: opa.mathematics.set-theory.borels-conjecture
  Status: Open

  A set of real numbers is "strong measure zero" if it can be covered by intervals of any prescribed shrinking sizes. Borel conjectured in 1919 that only countable sets can be this "thin." This turns out to be independent of the usual axioms of set theory (ZFC).

